# 6. Rebuild Liability as exposure stack, not recommendation engine

Liability should not sound like it recommends coverage. It should show:

```text
Projected Exposure
   ↓
Existing Coverage
   ↓
Illustrative Gap
   ↓
Umbrella Block Translation
```

Recommended pipeline:

```text
Client income/assets
   ↓
Disposable income estimate
   ↓
Projected garnishment exposure
   ↓
At-risk assets
   ↓
Total illustrative exposure
   ↓
Existing auto/home/umbrella coverage
   ↓
Illustrative umbrella coverage level rounded to $1M blocks
```

Core rules:

```ts
disposableIncome = grossIncome × disposableIncomeRatio
```

```ts
wageExposure =
  Σ disposableIncome × growthFactor × garnishmentRate
```

```ts
umbrellaBlockLevel =
  ceil(rawIllustrativeNeed / 1_000_000) × 1_000_000
```

Language must stay illustrative:

Bad:

```text
Recommended Umbrella
You should purchase $X
```

Good:

```text
Illustrative Umbrella Coverage Level
Rounded to common $1M umbrella policy blocks.
```

This should be enforced in a copy/disclosure layer, not manually repeated inside components.

