# 7. Rebuild Unemployment around household income concentration

Unemployment should not use the same 6-month ideal for every household.

The proper engine:

```text
Primary income + spouse income + monthly expenses
   ↓
Convert income to estimated net monthly income
   ↓
Assume highest earner loses income
   ↓
Calculate remaining income coverage %
   ↓
Map coverage % to ideal reserve months
   ↓
Calculate minimum, ideal, gap, excess
   ↓
Render gauge + explanation
```

Core formula:

```ts
remainingIncomeCoveragePct =
  remainingNetMonthlyIncome / monthlyExpenses
```

Reserve rule:

```ts
if coveragePct < 0.33 => 6 months
if coveragePct < 0.50 => 5 months
if coveragePct < 0.67 => 4 months
else => 3 months
```

Outputs should include:

```ts
type UnemploymentReserveResult = {
  primaryNetMonthlyIncome: number
  secondaryNetMonthlyIncome: number
  incomeAtRisk: number
  remainingIncome: number
  remainingIncomeCoveragePct: number
  minimumReserveMonths: number
  idealReserveMonths: number
  minimumReserveTarget: number
  idealReserveTarget: number
  reserveGap: number
  excessReserve: number
}
```

The UI should explain why the target is 3, 4, 5, or 6 months. That is more advisor-friendly than a static gauge.

