# 9. Add an advisor-compliance copy layer

This matters because the advisor specifically called out wording like “Recommended Umbrella.”

Create a file like:

```text
src/domain/copy/advisorSafeCopy.ts
```

With reusable language:

```ts
export const complianceCopy = {
  illustrativeOnly:
    "This is an illustrative gap analysis and not a formal recommendation.",

  umbrellaBlocks:
    "Umbrella coverage is commonly issued in $1M blocks. This value rounds the illustrative gap to the next $1M block.",

  wageGarnishment:
    "Uses a simplified disposable-earnings proxy for illustrative purposes. Actual garnishment limits vary by jurisdiction and case type.",

  lifeDeathBenefit:
    "Death benefit needed is estimated from the present value of modeled annual income gaps."
}
```

Then components reference approved copy instead of writing new language ad hoc.

