# 14. Recommended rebuild phases

## Phase 1 — Methodology stabilization

Goal: stop contradictions.

Implement:

* shared assumption layer,
* annual/monthly gap schedules,
* Life Safe Income Coverage refactor,
* Liability disposable-income refactor,
* Unemployment dynamic reserve refactor,
* copy cleanup.

This is the advisor-adherence phase.

## Phase 2 — Domain architecture refactor

Goal: remove calculation logic from UI.

Implement:

* pure module engines,
* view model builders,
* formula registry,
* compliance copy layer,
* persisted data migration helpers.

## Phase 3 — UI simplification

Goal: make advisor workflows cleaner.

Implement:

* assumptions panels,
* clearer input grouping,
* chart/metric alignment,
* better “why this number” microcopy,
* remove deprecated fields.

## Phase 4 — Scenario/report readiness

Goal: prepare for client-ready outputs.

Implement:

* scenario snapshots,
* saved assumptions,
* export-ready result objects,
* advisor notes,
* report templates.

