# 15. Best long-term architecture

The final tool should conceptually look like this:

```text
src/
  app/
    routes/
    pages/

  components/
    ui/
    charts/
    metric-cards/

  domain/
    assumptions/
    financial/
    copy/
    formulas/
    gap-analysis/
    modules/
      life/
      disability/
      liability/
      unemployment/
      offensive/

  features/
    client-profile/
    scenario-builder/
    module-workspace/
    reports/

  lib/
    store/
    persistence/
    migration/
    formatting/
```

The key rule:

> `features/` handles product workflow.
> `domain/` handles truth, formulas, and methodology.
> `components/` handles display only.
> `lib/` handles infrastructure.

---

# Bottom-line recommendation

You should not keep patching each module independently. The advisor comments show the app needs a **methodology-first architecture**.

The optimal rebuild is:

1. Make **gap schedules** the source of truth.
2. Centralize **assumptions**.
3. Move all formulas into **pure domain engines**.
4. Generate all cards/charts/narratives from a single **view model**.
5. Add a **formula registry** and **advisor-safe copy layer**.
6. Keep the product framed as an **illustrative gap analysis tool**, not a recommendation engine.
7. Add lightweight local-storage migration so old field names do not poison the new methodology.

That architecture will make the tool easier to maintain, easier for advisors to trust, and much less likely to produce contradictions like “fully covered” while a chart still shows a gap.
